00c9tienne Thobois, attributed the huge interest to the lingering impact of London 2012 and the fact that the French capital is so close.\", \"from\": 298, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 324, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999985053166057, \"rank\": 1.1340667359542684e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999986532657, \"rank\": 1.3467099603080956e-09, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9977893418236173, \"rank\": 0.0022155556679415074, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 467, \"end\": 473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6899153272140527, \"rank\": 0.4285395434947071, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a trip\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 316}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c9tienne Thobois\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 375}, {\"ngram\": \"the huge interest\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"the lingering impact\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 429}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thobois said: \\\"Yes, Britain is the first market by far outside of France, with almost 500,000 tickets sold.\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 6